description: A photographer snapped the rare phenomenon which occurs when a tornado forms over water.
title: Rare sighting of a waterspout in County Kerry
title_page: Rare sighting of a waterspout in County Kerry - BBC News
maintext: As they develop, funnel-shaped clouds sometimes extend from the base of the cloud and it is only when these funnel clouds touch the ground or sea that we get a tornado or waterspout.
